LeoF
\n<Leo>What is this? A moon shaped rock?
LeoF
\n<Leo>Is this even worth anything?
\n<???>Were you hoping for something more?
LeoF
\n<Leo>Huh? Who said that?
\n<???>Hm, you can't see me yet? Just my voice?
LeoF
\n<Leo>This voice... it's in my head... am I sick?
\n<???>You're not sick you fool. I'm speaking directly into your mind.
Only you can hear me.
LeoF
\n<Leo>Are you this stone?
\n<???>Sadly I don't have a physical body, I'm not a dumb rock.
That would be stupid.
LeoF
\n<Leo>This... this is a bit much. Where are you?
\n<???>I'm around you, or am I inside you? Like some magical ghost.
I'm just there you know? Hard to really explain.
\n<???>I don't know why you can hear me now. You've gotten stronger it seems.
LeoF
\n<Leo>What are you talking about? Like I could believe this
nonsense. What kind of magic are you using?
\n<???>Yeah, didn't expect you to believe it right away.
\n<???>Let's say I'm a type of spirit, people call us \c[10]Phantoms\c[0].
Not to be mistaken as an actual phantom. My name is Torn.
LeoF
\n<Leo>Still not falling for it, show yourself.
\n<Torn>Sigh... I'm not getting to you am I? I can't reveal myself
because you haven't awakened me fully.
\n<Torn>Since you can hear me, this means trouble.
LeoF
\n<Leo>What are you saying? Trouble for who?
\n<Torn>A \c[3]Phantom User\c[0], which is what you are, does not gain his
phantom unless something extremely dangerous is taking place.
\n<Torn>I'm not talking about some drowning kid either. Something that threatens
your life.
LeoF
\n<Leo>I'm not following, I'm under no threat right now.
\n<Torn>Which is probably why you can only hear me. You haven't woken up
to your powers yet. But I don't have enough time to explain.
LeoF
\n<Leo>You don't have time to explain? It sure looks like we have
plenty of time to me.
LeoF
\n<Leo>W-what was that? It felt like a wave hit the tower.
\n<Torn>Remember how the water level was a bit low?
LeoF
\n<Leo>It should still be low, what does that have to do
with the shaking?
\n<Torn>That was the effect of the moon. Well, the effect of someone
tampering with it.
\n<Torn>Now that it's night time, the moon should be directly above
us. What do you think think happened to that missing water?
LeoF
\n<Leo>It would raise up? Wait, it wouldn't just return to normal
right? It would be way higher.
\n<Torn>The water was only low around the tower, meaning it's directed here.
LeoF
\n<Leo>So I'm the only one in trouble? I should be able to
wait out the night then, and leave in the morning.
\n<Torn>I never said it was just you, it's the total opposite.
The moon was tampered with, the water level being effected was on purpose.
LeoF
\n<Leo>What would someone gain from that?
\n<Torn>Someone is trying to keep you here, at least for tonight.
Let me tell you, not just anyone can have an effect on the moon.
\n<Torn>It takes a extremely high amount of magic to do something like that.
LeoF
\n<Leo>If that's the case, something must be going on, and
someone doesn't want me to be a part of it.
\n<Torn>That's why I said I had no time to expain you fool!
Now hurry, we already wasted too much time. Get out of here!
LeoF
\n<Leo>You don't have to yell inside my head, I'm going!
